Drogon AI Assistant 🐉
Complete Setup and Usage Guide

Drogon is a personal AI assistant written in Python. It can listen to your voice, accept typed commands, open applications, search the internet, and generate Model UN speeches using OpenAI. This guide explains every step from installation to daily use.

What Drogon Can Do

After setup, Drogon can:

Wake up when you say "Hello"
Accept text commands
Open Chrome, YouTube, Spotify, Notepad, Calculator, Paint, and Command Prompt
Open Documents, Downloads, and Desktop folders
Search Google
Search YouTube
Generate MUN opening speeches using OpenAI
Save generated speeches into a file called speech.txt
Step 1: Install Python 3.12
Open the Microsoft Store.
Search for Python 3.12.
Install the 64-bit version.
After installation, open Command Prompt and type:
py -3.12 --version

You should see something like:

Python 3.12.x

If you see that version number, Python is installed correctly.

Step 2: Create the Project Folder
Open File Explorer.
Go to Documents.
Create a new folder named:
Drogon-AI

Inside this folder, you will place all project files.

Step 3: Create the Main Python File
Open Notepad.
Paste the full drogon.py code that was provided.
Click File → Save As.
Choose the Drogon-AI folder.
File name:
drogon.py
Change Save as type to All Files (.).
Save the file.
Step 4: Create requirements.txt
Open Notepad again.
Paste:
openai
SpeechRecognition
pyttsx3
pyaudio
Save it as:
requirements.txt

inside the Drogon-AI folder.

Step 5: Install All Required Libraries

Open Command Prompt and run:

cd %USERPROFILE%\Documents\Drogon-AI
py -3.12 -m pip install -r requirements.txt

Wait until all packages finish installing.

Step 6: Get Your OpenAI API Key
Go to https://platform.openai.com
Sign in with your OpenAI account.
Open API Keys.
Click Create new secret key.
Copy the key immediately.

It will look similar to:

sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

Never share this key publicly.

Step 7: Store the API Key Securely

In Command Prompt, run:

setx OPENAI_API_KEY "your_actual_api_key_here"

Replace your_actual_api_key_here with your real key.

After running the command:

Close Command Prompt completely.
Open a new Command Prompt window.

This makes the API key available to Drogon without putting it inside the code.

Step 8: Run Drogon

In Command Prompt:

cd %USERPROFILE%\Documents\Drogon-AI
py -3.12 drogon.py

Drogon will start and ask:

Choose mode (voice/text):
Step 9: Using Text Mode

Type:

text

Then you can enter commands directly.

Examples:

open chrome
open youtube
open spotify
search latest AI news
youtube python tutorial
speech cyber warfare and international security
exit

This mode is useful when testing new features.

Step 10: Using Voice Mode

Type:

voice

Drogon will say:

Voice mode activated. Say Hello to wake me up.
Example Conversation

You:

Hello

Drogon:

Drogon awakened. What do you command?

You:

Open Chrome

Drogon will open Chrome.

